
[1]mat

   MAT, n. [L. matta.]

   1. A texture of sedge, rushes, flags, husks, straw, or other material,
   to be laid on a floor for cleaning the boots and shoes of those who
   enter a house, and for other purposes.

   2. A web of rope-yard, used in ships to secure the standing rigging
   from the friction of the yards, &c.

                    MAT, v.t. To cover or lay with mats.

   1. To twist together; to interweave like a mat; to entangle.

   And o'er his eyebrows hung his matted hair.

   2. To press together; to lay flat; as matted grass.
